  <discussion>Native from the Black Sea and Transcaucasus to coastal southern and western Europe,
        and also well established as a ruderal in central Europe, Glaucium flavum has spread far
        beyond that range as a ballast waif and occasional garden escape. It should be expected
        elsewhere in the flora.</discussion>
